enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve updating the state of the current iterator, which is crucial for the correct functioning of the remove operation.
The findNextByIterator method is used to traverse the iterators, which is a prerequisite for the remove operation to know which element to remove.
The next method is closely related to the remove method as it determines the last element returned, which is the element that the remove method will remove.
The hasNext method checks if there are more elements in the iteration, which is a precondition for the remove method to be called without throwing an exception.
